  <prompt>
    Update SmartTodo Code Page to query `sprk_todo` as the kanban data source. Remove the `todoflag=true` filter and all references to `sprk_event` in the kanban path. Update column rendering to use the new entity's attribute names (already mirrors prior shape — `sprk_todocolumn`, `sprk_todopinned`, etc.). Verify network trace shows only `/api/data/v9.x/sprk_todos` requests from the kanban path.
  </prompt>

  <role>Spaarke Code Page developer with Fluent v9 + Dataverse Web API expertise.</role>

  <goal>All kanban data queries hit `/api/data/v9.x/sprk_todos`. Zero queries to `sprk_events` from the kanban path. Existing kanban behavior (drag, pin, threshold scoring) preserved.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>The SmartTodo Code Page was the original event-coupled surface. Phase 3 is its first-class repoint. The `sprk_todo` entity has the same kanban-behavior fields (mirrored from `sprk_event`), so the UI logic carries over with only the entity name changing.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-11">All kanban queries hit `sprk_todo`; no `todoflag=true` filter remains.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">Fluent v9 + semantic tokens + Griffel only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="OS-1">No compat shims (no parallel `sprk_event` query path "just in case").</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md</file>
